According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of motorists reported more than once for driving drunk take the car again.
The alcolock would avoid it since it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the rate of alcohol in exhaled air and prevents starting the car if the driver does not blow abtes; or when an alcohol concentration is detected is higher than allowed.
Its cost is more than 1,000 euros and would be at the expense of the sanctioned.
A 2007 U.S. study showed that vehicles equipped with these devices reduce infractions by up to 65% during the first year of implementation.
And in Spain it is estimated that it could save the lives of 115 people each year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: addressing those behaviors before they result in criminal offences.
And facilitate its implementation, since the legal reform can be done by the ordinary way, and, however, the necessary reform by the criminal way requires a reform in an organic law.
The device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any commercial modality, although it has already been experimentally implemented in some commercial and public service vehicles.
