What were they producing at the invoice factory Zuschlag & amp; Co. ?
Very soon, on October 8, criminal proceedings will begin against János Zuschlag and his accomplices.
The politician and his accomplices are accused of committing fraud of significant harm, in a business manner, continuously and in an organized way in addition to other crimes, including the falsification of documents.
According to the Prosecutor ' s Office, they used the funds obtained in public tenders for their own purposes, often justifying the fulfillment of tasks with false invoices.
The public funds and those of the municipalities - in their entirety some 65 million HUF - stopped partly in the treasury of the organization Fiatal Baloldal and partly in the pockets of private individuals.
The method, which was also made known by the researchers, was to justify the collection of funds obtained in public tenders with false invoices behind which there was no real execution, the different associations never fulfilled their obligations assumed.
According to the indictment, most of the invoices were fake.
For this they obtained the heels in the market of the Józsefváros District and the circular seals were manufactured in the city of Kiskunhalas.
And the question that in the name of which company the counterfeit invoice should be made was decided among others on that tour of the Upper Balaton Region where János Zuschlag sent István Lados.
The latter confessed that for this purpose he had to choose hostels and restaurants.
He asked for an invoice for his consumptions and these served as a model to prepare the invoices that they presented among others in the competitions of the Ministry of Youth and Sports Affairs, in the Ministry of Social and Labor Affairs, as well as in the City of the Capital.
These invoices were mostly signed by István Lados and his accomplice András <0xC5><0x90>ri, who according to our information rather wrote the reports necessary to obtain the public subsidies.
During one of his "study trips" Lados chose a brewery.
According to two invoices issued in 2003 by Zuschlag and his accomplices, this gastronomic center provided food for a group of ninety people of the Biztos Pont Egyesület Association.
However - according to the manager of the center - so many people do not fit in that place at once.
Similarly, the invoice issued in the summer of 2002 for the Jobb Jöv<0xC5><0x91>ért Foundation - later called Együtt to Harmadik Évezredert - was full of formal and contextual errors.
For a hostel in the town of Badacsonytomaj had only three rooms and more than ten people could not stay there in one night, yet on the bill there were a hundred and thirty people.
But the fancy invoice manufacturers also exaggerated when they pointed to the Pigal Kft. gastronomic center, because in the bookstore of the same - according to the information given to the Prosecutor's Office - there were no documents in the name of Jobb Jöv<0xC5><0x91>ért and Hoppá.
Gy<0xC5><0x91>z<0xC5><0x91> Farkas, the company’s manager, told hvg.hu that when he was summoned by the prosecution and shown the invoices, he already knew they were fake documents.
"On the stamp the name of our company and the NIF appeared in the wrong place."
He added: in addition to the formal problems, he also did not agree that according to the invoice a hundred people were accommodated, since they have only eleven rooms in which not so many people can fit.
In addition, meals were also included in the invoice, while the restaurant has not worked for a long time.
Enthusiastic invoice makers were also not informed that the travel agency chosen in Budapest exclusively organizes trips abroad, so on the cash payment invoice they foolishly indicated as a service a trip within Hungary, which also did not coincide with the practice of issuing invoices of the agency.
In addition - as it was known during the investigation - they included VAT in the document as well, despite the fact that trips outside the territory of the European Union were exempt from taxes.
Among other things, the VAT measure was also incorrect in the four documents issued by the Hotel Révfülöp Kft. for the Jobb Jöv<0xC5><0x91>ért foundation, since the services of this company are not charged with a 25 but only with 15 percent VAT, in addition the hotel employees only issued invoices made by machine but the invoice was manual.
Besides the "shippers" made other errors also, as in the case of a company in which they put in the invoice as activity carried out the transport by road to which - it was known during the investigations of the prosecution - does not realize the company founded as consultant of investments.
Also due to formal differences - inadequate format of the invoice, false stamp - it was known that the invoices issued for Együtt to Harmadik Évezredert Alapítvány, for XXI. Századi Kulturális Egyesület and for Biztos Pont are false.
As in the case of Ravenna Bt. or the Kunfehertó Sports Camp, whose representatives denied having issued those invoices.
The counterfeiters also did not pay attention to the fact that when the group of Fiatal Városért Egyesület ate there (2001) the HIB Kft. of Nyíregyháza was in the process of liquidation, which is why the person in charge of the liquidation process - according to our information - denied having issued such a document.
They consciously issued the invoices
Another group of manufacturers of fake invoices are those who were aware that they had to issue fictitious invoices.
The Esély Budapestért Alapítvány Foundation, at the request of Fiatal Baloldal - Ifjú Szocialisták, issued an invoice worth about four million HUF on behalf of the Együtt Foundation to Harmadik Évezredért.
