A written version of the law has been prepared for the $700 billion financial rescue package that will be applied in several phases in order to buy bad credit from banks.
In the first phase half of the money will be spent.
According to East Coast schedule during the new consultations that lasted until after midnight on Saturday, congressional leaders reached an agreement around the $700 billion total financial rescue package, after several days of discussion.
“We have made significant progress,” said Nancy Pelosi, Democratic president of the U.S. Congress, saying the agreement had only yet to be formalized in a document.
The commitment made on the package was supported by both presidential candidates, Barack Obama and John McCain.
Henry Paulson, the Minister of Finance, speaking on the outcome of the compromise stated: this program will work and be efficient but more measures are needed. According to Pelosi, it is not about saving Wall Street, but about turning the cart of the economy.
The written version of the package was published before the opening of the Asian markets, that is, on Sunday before 8 p.m., according to Washington time (i.e. before 2 a.m. on Monday, according to Central European time), without causing a spectacular jump in the stock markets.
On the bill called the 2008 Economic Stabilization Emergency Act, the U.S. Congress will vote on Monday, first, and then the Senate.
President George W. Bush on Saturday night consulted with Pelosi and then the White House also welcomed the news about the deal.
"We are pleased with the progress made overnight and highly appreciate the efforts of both parties to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy," White House spokesman Tony Fratto said.
The program is different from the Bush administration’s original proposal to spend all $700 billion to buy bad credit fund securities.
Now only half of the $700 billion can be spent, using $250 billion immediately after Congress votes, probably on Monday, of this sum the Ministry of Finance will buy credit fund securities, of poor rating and the fate of another $100 billion depends on the decision of the president.
This program will be controlled by a special body, in which the president of the Federal Reserve will also participate.
The other half of the $700 billion could be spent after a new Congressional decision.
According to the law, the Ministry of Finance can apply a combined tactic: you can simultaneously buy bad credits, mortgages and securities of credit fund, in addition to other credits of "poisonous" type as well.
The purchase can be made in auctions or directly - informed competent people of the ministry.
The law allows affected companies to participate in an insurance program where the finance portfolio guarantees the worrying elements, for which the companies will pay the amount corresponding to the foreseeable damages.
Henry Paulson asserted: the law thus ensures the necessary financial means, which can reach up to 700 billion dollars to meet the urgent needs of the American financial system, whether it is the purchase of bad financial means, their insurance or the prevention of risks that could cause the collapse of some large financial institutions.
We do everything necessary to be ready to introduce the law as soon as they sign it.
Instead, the heads of the banks that are in distress and await the help of the state will be able to count on the official limitation of their compensations, which the American slang simply calls gold parachutes.
Only in certain cases will payments be limited, and the limitations depend on the form of aid provided by the Ministry of Finance.
The limitation means that if the ministry buys in the framework of an auction, an extra tax will be imposed for gold parachutes, unless the bank’s failed boss retires.
By directly buying the bad credits the government will aggressively intervene to ensure that the bosses’ compensations are not exaggerated.
In addition to the above, existing gold parachute contracts will not be changed, the limitations refer only to new contracts to stimulate participation in the programme as well.
This is the first case in U.S. history that a legal limitation on CEOs’ revenues will be in place, said Democrat Barney Frank, chairman of the congressional committee responsible for financial services.
The State will also have the right to acquire shares of the banks participating in the program, thus reducing the risk of taxpayers, since ultimately they can even make profits from the transaction as soon as the economy recovers and with it the bank.
According to the bill in the next five years, the president will have to submit to Congress a proposal on how to return to taxpayers the losses of the financial sector.
Of course, there were those on both sides who expressed reservations about the project.
This is not what the American citizens entrusted to us, that is, taxpayer dollars are not being protected,” said California Republican Congressman Darrell Issa.
